Acceptance Criteria (user perspective) (for 25 Mar build):
1. Surge & Sam can provide onboarding information to me (via a call). Which is saved, normalised, stored by the system (e.g. user onboarding files).
2. Surge & Sam can view 3 requested signals via the signal preview web ui. No login required. On  my computer. With 3 key interactions: 1-Signal card overview. 2-Signal card expanded. 3-View different signal card.
3. On the signal preview screen, I can toggle between Surge & Sam view
4. Surge & Sam can view 3 recommended signals (with sufficient data). With 3 key interactions.1-Signal card overview. 2-Signal card expanded (including why it’s recommended). 3-View different signal card.
5. Surge & Sam can view 3 recommended signals (with insufficient data). 1-Signal card overview. 2-Signal card expanded (why it’s recommended, what data is missing, tips for practically sourcing the data). 3-View different signal card.
6 The data flow & architecture, from ingesting onboarding files and user data files, to agent processing, agent outputs, is explained clearly. Is designed in a modular way where it it easy to amend instructions in order to fine tune the data Surge & Sam sees
7. Surge & Sam can view 1 requested signal (with insufficient data). When the signal card is expanded, it shows why this signal matters in context, what data is missing, and tips for practically sourcing the data.

The goal of this set of acceptance criteria is meant to show the core data that delivers the core value prop of the Camino product. 